# MINI_SOC_SPEC_v1.0

## 1. Introduction

### 1.1 Purpose

This document defines the architecture and functional specification of the Mini SoC used for learning SoC design and verification concepts.

The objective of this project is to provide a compact yet realistic SoC containing multiple APB peripherals accessed through an AXI-Lite to APB bridge.
The design is intentionally simplified while retaining key concepts found in industrial SoCs.

### 1.2 Scope

The Mini SoC shall include:

* AXI-Lite to APB Bridge
* APB Interconnect / Address Decoder
* GPIO Controller
* Timer Controller
* DMA Controller

The SoC shall support:

* Register-based programming model
* Interrupt generation
* APB protocol transactions
* AXI-Lite protocol transactions
* Control, Status, and Configuration registers

---

# 2. System Overview

The Mini SoC consists of three APB peripherals connected to a common APB bus. Software accesses all peripherals through an AXI-Lite interface.

## 2.1 High-Level Architecture

```
                 AXI-Lite Master
                        |
                        |
              +------------------+
              | AXI-Lite to      |
              | APB Bridge       |
              +--------+---------+
                       |
                    APB Bus
                       |
    +------------------+------------------+
    |                  |                  |
    |                  |                  |
  GPIO               TIMER              DMA
APB Slave          APB Slave         APB Slave
```

---

# 3. Clock and Reset Architecture

## 3.1 Clock

A single clock domain shall be used.

Signal Name:

```
PCLK
```

Description:

```
Primary clock for all peripherals.
```

Clocking:

```
Rising-edge triggered.
```

---

## 3.2 Reset

Signal Name:

```
PRESETn
```

Description:

```
Active-low synchronous reset.
```

Behavior:

```
PRESETn = 0

    All registers reset to default values.
    All interrupts cleared.
    DMA state machine returns to IDLE.

PRESETn = 1

    Normal operation.
```

---

# 4. Bus Architecture

## 4.1 AXI-Lite Interface

The Mini SoC shall expose a single AXI-Lite slave interface.

Supported Features:

* Single-beat transactions
* 32-bit addressing
* 32-bit data width
* Separate read/write channels

Unsupported Features:

* Burst transactions
* IDs
* Out-of-order completion
* Outstanding transactions

---

## 4.2 APB Interface

All peripherals shall implement APB3 slave interfaces.

Supported Signals:

```
PSEL
PENABLE
PWRITE
PADDR[31:0]
PWDATA[31:0]
PRDATA[31:0]
PREADY
PSLVERR
```

---

# 5. Address Map

| Peripheral | Base Address | Address Range             |
| ---------- | ------------ | ------------------------- |
| GPIO       | 0x0000_0000  | 0x0000_0000 - 0x0000_00FF |
| TIMER      | 0x0000_1000  | 0x0000_1000 - 0x0000_10FF |
| DMA        | 0x0000_2000  | 0x0000_2000 - 0x0000_20FF |

All accesses outside these regions shall generate an error response.

---

# 6. GPIO Controller Specification

## 6.1 Purpose

Provides basic General Purpose Input/Output functionality.

Supports:

* Pin direction control
* Input sampling
* Output driving
* Interrupt generation

---

## 6.2 External Signals

Inputs:

```
gpio_in[7:0]
```

Outputs:

```
gpio_out[7:0]
```

Interrupt:

```
gpio_irq
```

---

## 6.3 Register Map

| Offset | Register Name |
| ------ | ------------- |
| 0x00   | GPIO_CTRL     |
| 0x04   | GPIO_DIR      |
| 0x08   | GPIO_DATA_OUT |
| 0x0C   | GPIO_DATA_IN  |
| 0x10   | GPIO_STATUS   |

---

## 6.4 Functional Behavior

When GPIO is enabled:

* GPIO_DATA_OUT drives output pins configured as outputs.
* GPIO_DATA_IN reflects input pins.
* Interrupt status may be set by hardware events.

---

# 7. Timer Controller Specification

## 7.1 Purpose

Provides programmable countdown timer functionality.

Supports:

* One-shot mode
* Periodic mode
* Timeout interrupt

---

## 7.2 Interrupt

Output:

```
timer_irq
```

---

## 7.3 Register Map

| Offset | Register Name |
| ------ | ------------- |
| 0x00   | TIMER_CTRL    |
| 0x04   | TIMER_LOAD    |
| 0x08   | TIMER_COUNT   |
| 0x0C   | TIMER_STATUS  |

---

## 7.4 Functional Behavior

When enabled:

* TIMER_COUNT loads from TIMER_LOAD.
* Counter decrements every clock cycle.
* Timeout event generated at count value zero.
* Timeout status bit set.
* Interrupt generated if enabled.

Periodic mode:

* Automatically reload TIMER_LOAD.

One-shot mode:

* Stop counting after timeout.

---

# 8. DMA Controller Specification

## 8.1 Purpose

Provides simplified DMA operation for verification learning.

Actual memory movement is not implemented.

The DMA models a transfer operation through an internal state machine.

---

## 8.2 Interrupt

Output:

```
dma_irq
```

---

## 8.3 Register Map

| Offset | Register Name |
| ------ | ------------- |
| 0x00   | DMA_CTRL      |
| 0x04   | DMA_SRC_ADDR  |
| 0x08   | DMA_DST_ADDR  |
| 0x0C   | DMA_SIZE      |
| 0x10   | DMA_STATUS    |

---

## 8.4 DMA State Machine

States:

```
IDLE
BUSY
DONE
ERROR
```

Operation:

1. Software programs source address.
2. Software programs destination address.
3. Software programs transfer size.
4. Software sets START bit.
5. DMA enters BUSY state.
6. Transfer completes after programmable delay.
7. DONE status bit asserted.
8. Interrupt generated if enabled.

---

# 9. Interrupt Architecture

The Mini SoC shall provide three independent interrupt outputs.

Signals:

```
gpio_irq
timer_irq
dma_irq
```

Interrupt sources:

GPIO:

```
GPIO_STATUS.irq_pending
```

Timer:

```
TIMER_STATUS.timeout
```

DMA:

```
DMA_STATUS.done
DMA_STATUS.error
```

Interrupts remain asserted until software clears the corresponding status bits.

---

# 10. Error Handling

APB accesses to undefined register addresses shall return:

```
PSLVERR = 1
```

AXI-Lite accesses to undefined address regions shall return:

```
SLVERR response
```

No data corruption shall occur during illegal accesses.

---

# 11. Reset Values Summary

GPIO Registers:

```
Reset value = 0x00000000
```

Timer Registers:

```
Reset value = 0x00000000
```

DMA Registers:

```
Reset value = 0x00000000
```

Interrupt outputs:

```
Deasserted after reset
```

DMA state:

```
IDLE after reset
```

---

# 12. Verification Objectives

The Mini SoC shall be verified for:

* Register functionality
* Reset behavior
* APB protocol compliance
* AXI-Lite protocol compliance
* Interrupt functionality
* Address decoding
* Error handling
* Functional coverage
* End-to-end SoC operation

End of Document
